text.tspan: XNOR gates perform multiply, popcnt (and acc) perform add.
Comparator performs activation - Sign() which is step approx of sigmoid.
16b threshold and acc width is for memmap convenience (max).
Something smaller like 8b is more realistic for buildability.
Most neuron inputs shouldn't need ff in a fclayer as they can share.
To use a stochastic approx of a sigmoid the gt comparator
should look like this, using an additional input which is
random in the interval of acc/2.
